modules.description: This module handles IP layer operations for both IPv4 and IPv6, including packet input demultiplexing, IP frame writing with fragmentation control, source address selection, and pseudoheader generation for checksums. It works with IP addresses, prefixes, and network buffers, providing direct access to interface configuration such as MTU and assigned IP prefixes. Concrete use cases include processing incoming IP packets, sending UDP or TCP packets with specified options, and determining source addresses for outgoing connections.

This module defines a network interface stack for virtualized networking, focusing on packet transmission and reception. It works with network device interfaces and packet buffers to manage communication in virtualized environments. Concrete use cases include implementing virtual network backends for hypervisors and handling network I/O in unikernels.
